    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_RetrieveAvailablePublishedMonthBetweenDecAndFeb",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve distinct published billing periods from a database table, specifically for the months of December and February, across two fiscal years. It calculates the billing periods for December of the fiscal year two years prior and February of the previous fiscal year, then filters and returns the available published months within this range."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving basic SQL operations such as variable declaration, simple arithmetic calculations, and a single SELECT query with a WHERE clause. It does not involve complex logic, multiple joins, or subqueries, which keeps the complexity low."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@fy AS INT",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This parameter represents the fiscal year. It is used to calculate the billing periods for December and February across two fiscal years. The fiscal year is expected to be an integer value."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "4. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "orderedList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Set Transaction Isolation Level",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure sets the transaction isolation level to READ UNCOMMITTED, allowing the query to read uncommitted changes from other transactions. This can help reduce locking and blocking but may result in reading dirty data."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Variable Declaration and Initialization",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": Two variables, "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@publishedBillingPeriodDEC",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@publishedBillingPeriodFEB",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", are declared to store the billing periods for December and February, respectively. These are calculated using the input fiscal year ("
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@fy",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "):"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "listItem",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "paragraph",
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "@publishedBillingPeriodDEC",
                          "marks": [
                            {
                              "type": "code"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": " is calculated as December of two fiscal years prior ("
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "(@fy - 2) * 100 + 12",
                          "marks": [
                            {
                              "type": "code"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": ")."
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "listItem",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "paragraph",
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "@publishedBillingPeriodFEB",
                          "marks": [
                            {
                              "type": "code"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": " is calculated as February of the previous fiscal year ("
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "(@fy - 1) * 100 + 2",
                          "marks": [
                            {
                              "type": "code"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": ")."
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Data Retrieval",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure queries the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Published_MonthlyPublishedSummaryData",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " table to select distinct "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "PublishedBillingPeriod",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " values that fall between the calculated December and February billing periods. The results are ordered in descending order."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "5. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "READ UNCOMMITTED Isolation Level",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": While this level can improve performance by reducing locking, it may lead to reading uncommitted or dirty data, which could affect data accuracy."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Indexing",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The performance of the SELECT query can be improved if the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "PublishedBillingPeriod",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " column is indexed, especially given the ORDER BY clause."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Calculation Overhead",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The arithmetic operations for calculating billing periods are minimal and unlikely to impact performance significantly."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Potential Issues or Risks"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Dirty Reads",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": Using the READ UNCOMMITTED isolation level can lead to dirty reads, where the data read might not be committed and could change, leading to potential inconsistencies."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Data Type Mismatch",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure assumes that "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "PublishedBillingPeriod",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " is compatible with the VARCHAR(6) type. If the actual data type or format differs, it could lead to errors or unexpected results."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Fiscal Year Assumptions",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The logic assumes a specific format for fiscal years and billing periods. Any changes in business rules or data format could necessitate changes to the procedure."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Lack of Error Handling",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure does not include error handling mechanisms, which could be a risk if unexpected issues arise during execution."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "7. Stored Procedure Definition"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "codeBlock",
      "attrs": {
        "language": "sql"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CREATE PROCEDURE [prerequisite].[USP_RetrieveAvailablePublishedMonthBetweenDecAndFeb]\n(\r\n    @fy AS INT\r\n)\r\nAS\r\nBEGIN\r\n\tSET NOCOUNT ON;\r\n\tSET TRANSACTION ISOLATION LEVEL READ UNCOMMITTED;\r\n\r\n    DECLARE @publishedBillingPeriodDEC AS VARCHAR(6), @publishedBillingPeriodFEB AS VARCHAR(6);\r\n\r\n    SELECT @publishedBillingPeriodDEC = CAST(((@fy - 2) * 100 + 12) AS VARCHAR(6)), @publishedBillingPeriodFEB = CAST(((@fy - 1) * 100 + 2) AS VARCHAR(6));\r\n\r\n    SELECT DISTINCT PublishedBillingPeriod AS AvailablePublishedMonth\r\n    FROM EC3DB.Published_MonthlyPublishedSummaryData\r\n    WHERE PublishedBillingPeriod >= @publishedBillingPeriodDEC \r\n\t\tAND PublishedBillingPeriod <= @publishedBillingPeriodFEB \r\n    ORDER BY AvailablePublishedMonth DESC;\r\nEND;\r"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
